"Well, I'm going to bed, you can try to break in if you want, but I'm not going to be up for a
ny longer, spoke the 92nd little pig to the wolf". And sure enough, they went into the comfort of their bed, wondering a bit if the wolf would break into their house, while they slumbered.

They blew on the doors, the outside walls, and even tried scratching the windows, all seemingly resistant to his claws and might. The wolf decided to try a different approach.
